parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become stuck or inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract
the seat belt is stuck
the seat belt cable is jammed
the seat belt is extremely tight
the seat belt broke
the automatic seat belt retractor does not retract.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt track can cause the seat belt to become stuck or inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt rail is worn
the cable is jammed in the rail
the seat belt is stuck
the seat belt broke.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt motor can cause the seat belt to become stuck or inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The automatic seat belt motor is stuck
the seat belt does not retract
the seat belt is stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to control, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates
the transmission fails to shift into gear
the transmission shifts roughly
the transmission has a burnt oil smell
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the vehicle has a runaway acceleration problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down while in operation, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In severe cases, it can also cause electrical fires, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down while in operation
the ignition switch stays in the "on" position
the vehicle runs hot
there is a burning smell or smoke
the battery drains
the alternator fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical wiring issues can cause a range of problems, including short circuits, fires, and component failures, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The headlights or other electrical components malfunction
there is a burning smell or smoke
fuses trip
wires are damaged or burnt.
